The paper focuses on image restoration using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed framework involves optimization techniques (alternating minimization) and aggregation of information, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM).
